    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini Dei salvatoris Iesu Christi. Nos <rs
                            key="#Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis">vir gloriosissimus</rs>
                        <persName key="#Princeps #Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis" ref="#people/186"
                            >Sicardus</persName>, Dei providencia, Beneventane provincie <rs
                            key="#Princeps"> princeps</rs>, per rogum <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Other_palatine_officer" ref="#people/1905"
                            >Roffrid</persName>, <rs key="#Other_palatine_officer">referendarii</rs>
                        nostri, concedimus in <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Landed_possessions #Rivers #Mountains #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1900">Beatissimi Vincencii martyris</orgName>,
                        quod situm, est in finibus Samnie, iuxta <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/609">Vulturno</placeName>, ubi vir
                        verabi1is <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/1903">Epyphanius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>, orator noster, preesse videtur, <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terras</rs> cum <rs key="#Mountains"
                            >montibus</rs> uno se tenente, per hos fines: prima parte unde oritur
                            <rs key="#Rivers">riagine</rs>, que dicitur <placeName key="#Rivers"
                            ref="#places/2309">Ravennola</placeName>, et quomodo decurrit iam dicta
                        riagine de ipsa Ravennola, unde per tempus aqua decurrit, et qui exfinat
                        inter hec terra et <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terras</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Mountains">montes</rs>, quos concessos habet domnus <persName
                            key="#Princeps" ref="#people/303">Arichis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Princeps">princeps</rs> in iam prefato cenobio; de secunda parte
                        riagine, que dicitur Ravennola; da tercia parte unde incipit orire iam dicta
                        Ravennola, deinde incipiente circa <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terras</rs>
                        ei <rs key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention">montes
                            puplicos</rs>, usque in <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/2326">montem</placeName>, qui est super urbem <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Landed_possessions #Rivers" ref="#places/2300"
                            >Benafro</placeName>; quarta parte incipiente da iam dicto monte,
                        qualiter vadit per cilios aliorum moncium, usque in montem iam dicti
                        monasterii, qui est super terras, que vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1929">Arcora</geogName>, que est hereditas <orgName
                            key="#Mountains #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1904">Sancte Dei genitricis Marie</orgName>, que
                        nominatur <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#places/2330">Oliveto</placeName>, subiecta iam dicto monasterio,
                        et qualiter vadit circa <rs key="#Mountains">montes</rs> iam dicte <rs
                            key="#Churches">ecclesie</rs> Sancte Marie, et montes iam dicti cenobii.
                        Ideo in iam dicto monasterio concessimus in integrum iam dictas terras et
                        montes per iam dictos fines possidendum, in ea videlicet racione, ut a modo
                        et deinceps, per hoc nostrum roboratum, preceptum, cuncta, ut superius
                        leguntur, habere et possidere valeatis vos iam nominatus Epyphanius abbas,
                        atque successoribus et rectoribus iam dicti vestri monasterii, ita ut a
                        nullis ex nostris iudicibus, idest comitibus et gastaldeis, vel a
                        quibuscumque hominibus non habeatis de predictis terris et montibus aliquam
                        requisicionem vel molestacionem, sed perpetuis temporibus possideatis. Quod
                        vero <rs key="#Marquis’/ducal/princely_diploma">preceptum</rs> firmitatis,
                        ex iussione tue potestatis, scripsi ego <persName key="#Notary"><name
                                ref="Leodericus">Leodericus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>. <date>Actum <placeName key="#Palatium"
                                ref="#places/110">Benevento</placeName>, in sacro <rs
                                key="#Palatium">palacio</rs>, primo anno principatus eius, mense
                            magio, undecima indiccione</date>, feliciter. </ab>
